<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="correspond-vi">correspond <strong><em>vi</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌkɒrə'spɒnd/    美 /ˌkɔːrə'spɑːnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>相符合；相一致</strong></h4>
<p>to be the same as or match (agree)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your account of the events does not <strong>correspond with</strong> hers.
你对事情的描述与她说的不相符。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let your actions <strong>correspond to</strong> your words.
你要言行一致。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>相当；相类似</strong></h4>
<p>to be similar to：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The American Congress <strong>corresponds to</strong> the British Parliament.
美国国会相当于英国议会。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[正式用语]通信：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She corresponds regularly with her former teacher.
她和以前的老师定期通信。</p></div></div>